quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  3,52,"When ´Isa sensed kufr on their part, he said, ´Who will be my helpers to Allah?´ The disciples said, ´We are Allah´s helpers. We believe in Allah. Bear witness that we are Muslims"
  3,53,"Our Lord, we have iman in what You have sent down and have followed the Messenger, so write us down among the witnesses.´"
  3,54,They plotted and Allah plotted. But Allah is the best of plotters
  3,55,"When Allah said, ´´Isa, I will take you back and raise you up to Me and purify you of those who are kafir. And I will place the people who follow you above those who are kafir until the Day of Rising. Then you will all return to Me, and I will judge between you regarding the things about which you differed"
  3,56,"As for those who are kafir, I will punish them with a harsh punishment in this world and the Next World. They will have no helpers.´"
  3,57,"As for those who have iman and do right actions, We will pay them their wages in full. Allah does not love wrongdoers"
  3,58,That is what We recite to you of the Signs and the wise Reminder
  3,59,"The likeness of ´Isa in Allah´s sight is the same as Adam. He created him from earth and then He said to him, ´Be!´ and he was"
  3,60,It is the truth from your Lord so do not be among the doubters
  3,61,"If anyone argues with you about him after the knowledge that has come to you, say, ´Come then! Let us summon our sons and your sons, our women and your women, ourselves and yourselves. Then let us make earnest supplication and call down the curse of Allah upon the liars.´"
  3,62,"This is the true account: there is no other god besides Allah. Allah — He is the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  3,63,"And if they turn away, Allah knows the corrupters"
  3,64,"Say, ´People of the Book! come to a proposition which is the same for us and you — that we should worship none but Allah and not associate any partners with Him and not take one another as lords besides Allah.´ If they turn away, say, ´Bear witness that we are Muslims.´"
  3,65,´People of the Book! why do you argue concerning Ibrahim when the Torah and Injil were only sent down after him? Why do you not use your intellect
  3,66,You are people arguing about something of which you have no knowledge. Why do you argue about something of which you have no knowledge? Allah knows; you do not know.´
  3,67,Ibrahim was neither a Jew nor a Christian. but a man of pure natural belief — a Muslim. He was not one of the idolaters
  3,68,The people with the strongest claim to Ibrahim are those who followed him and this Prophet and those who have iman. Allah is the Protector of the muminun
  3,69,A group of the People of the Book would love to misguide you. They only misguide themselves but they are not aware of it
  3,70,People of the Book! why do you reject Allah´s Signs when you yourselves are there as witnesses
  3,71,People of the Book! why do you mix truth with falsehood and knowingly conceal the truth
  3,72,"A group of the People of the Book say, ´At the beginning of the day, you should claim to have iman in what was sent down to those who have iman, and then at the end of the day, you should reject it, so that hopefully they will revert"
  3,73,"Do not trust anyone except for those who follow your deen.´ Say, ´Allah´s guidance is true guidance. But you think it is impossible for anyone to be given the same as you were given, or to argue with you before your Lord.´ Say, ´All favour is in Allah´s Hand and He gives it to whoever He wills. Allah is All-Encompassing, All-Knowing"
  3,74,He picks out for His mercy whoever He wills. Allah´s favour is indeed immense.´